deck: French Cambodian actress who has appeared in comic related movies and television such as Daredevil as Elektra and G.I. Joe: Retaliation as Jinx
description:
Biography

Elodie Yung was born in Paris France, to a French mother and Cambodian father. Her date of birth is February 22, 1981. A graduate from London Academy of Music and Dramatic Art, Yung also has a Masters Degree in law, from University of La Sorbonne.

Elodie Yung has practiced Karate for over a decade and has a black belt in the discipline.

Acting Profile

Elodie Yung started with small roles in television, before appearing in larger movies. Some important career highlights include a role as Laura Maurier in Les bleus: premiers pas dans la police, and movies such as District 13: Ultimatum, starred as gang leader Tao. Appearing in The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo as Miriam Wu. As Hathor in 2016's Gods of Egypt.

Comic Related Movie Roles

Elektra Natchios

Elodie Yung portrays Elektra Natchios in the second season of Netflix's Daredevil television show. The character appears in 10 episodes of Season 2. The show has been a critical success as well as very popular among general audiences. The shows first season success creating much anticipation and hype for the casting and appearance of Elektra in the second series. Bill Sienkiewicz among many other industry professionals have praised her performance. She co-stars alongside Charlie Cox, Deborah Ann Woll, Elden Henson and Jon Bernthal.

Speaking of the character Elektra, Yung says "What I tried to capture by reading the comics is I wanted to keep the coldness that Elektra has. And I had conversations at length with Doug [Petrie] and Marco [Ramirez]. We think Elektra is kind of a sociopath. This world is a game for her. It's like a chess game, and what motivates her is what she wants."

Jinx

Elodie portrays the skilled ninja Jinx in 2013's G.I. Joe: Retaliation. Yung studied Wusha for the sword fighting elements in the movie. Speaking of the character, Yung says "Jinx wants to fight and she has an objective, and she’s fiery [laughs]. Whoever is in her way is not a problem to her, she’s so focused and she just wants to get straight to the point."
name: Elodie Yung

description:
Biography

Aubrey Plaza is an American actress and comedian known for her quirkiness, deadpan, and sarcastic personally as well as humor and wit. Aubrey Plaza has performed improv and sketch comedies at various esteemed venues. Born on June 26th, 1984, in Wilmington, Delaware, Aubrey Plaza has two sisters and is of Puerto Rican, Irish and English descent. She is a graduate of Ursuline Academy and New York's University Tisch School of the Arts.

Acting Profile

Aubrey Plaza has appeared in various television shows and movies, initially in minor roles, before progressively appearing in larger roles. Eventually starring in movies, such as Safety Not Guaranteed, where she is a lead protagonist and The To Do List, as lead role. Plaza also played April Ludgate in the popular and acclaimed television series Parks and Recreation. Her most recent movie roles include Mike and Dave Need Wedding Dates and the The Pistol Shrimps.

Comic Related Movie Roles

Julie Powers

Aubrey Plaza portrays Julie Powers in the 2010 movie adaptation of Scott Pilgrim, Scott Pilgrim vs. the World. Before filming Plaza received a "ten secret facts about Julie" to help her get into character, Plaza referring to some of them as silly, and some weird.

Eska

Aubrey Plaza is the voice of the character Eska in The Legend of Korra television show. Eska is the twin of Esme, both are powerful water benders related to main character Korra.

Lenny

Aubrey Plaza appears in the 2017 television show Legion, based on the Marvel comics X-Men mutant character of the same name. The show is produced by FX and Marvel Television, although it is not a part of the Marvel Cinematic Universe. In the show, she portrays Lenny, a character who turns out to be the Shadow King in disguise.
name: Aubrey Plaza
